The Herald Daniel Chigunwe Mash Central Correspondent A 95-year-old Mbire widow who leaves alone in a makeshift hut has appealed to the nation for help to build her a home. Kwedza Karombo of Chihumba village, ward under Chief Chitsungo said she received bricks from a member of the Apostolic Faith Mission (AFM) however she needs help with the building. Mbire villager Mr Fresher Muodza confirmed saying the widow is currently leaving in dilapidated small hut. ” We visited her yesterday, she expressed worry of the state of her home and called for assistance from well wishers,” said Muodza. Meanwhile, Zanu Pf provincial youth secretary for labour and social welfare Cde Brian Jonga said he is going to assist with cement whilst the province will try to raise funds to assist her.